---
import ServiceLayout from '@/layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Container from '@/components/ui/Container.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Cabinet Refacing"
  metaTitle="Cabinet Refacing Seattle WA | Kitchen Cabinet Makeover | Best KB Remodeling"
  metaDescription="Refresh your kitchen cabinets at a fraction of replacement cost. Expert cabinet refacing in Seattle with premium veneers, new doors, and hardware. Free estimates!"
  slug="cabinet-refacing"
  category="kitchen"
  heroImage="/images/service-cabinet-refacing.jpg"
  features={[
    'Precision measurement and template creation',
    'Premium real wood and laminate veneer application',
    'New custom-fit doors and drawer fronts',
    'Matching end panels and filler strips',
    'Soft-close hinge and drawer glide upgrades',
    'New hardware selection and installation',
    'Interior shelf and organizer additions',
  ]}
>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <p class="text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
      If your kitchen cabinets are structurally sound but visually tired, cabinet refacing offers a dramatic transformation at roughly half the cost of full cabinet replacement. This process replaces the visible surfaces — doors, drawer fronts, and face frames — while preserving the existing cabinet boxes, significantly reducing waste, timeline, and expense. It's one of the smartest kitchen upgrades available to Seattle homeowners.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      What Cabinet Refacing Involves
    </h2>
    <p>
      The refacing process begins with a thorough assessment of your existing cabinet boxes. We verify that the frames are level, square, and free of water damage or structural weakness. Once confirmed, we carefully remove the old doors, drawer fronts, and hardware. New veneer — either real wood or high-quality rigid thermofoil laminate — is applied to the visible face frames and exposed cabinet sides using professional-grade contact adhesive.
    </p>
    <p>
      Custom-fabricated doors and drawer fronts are then manufactured to precise measurements in the style and finish you've chosen. We install them with new concealed soft-close hinges and upgrade drawer slides to full-extension ball-bearing glides. Matching end panels, valances, and filler strips ensure a seamless, factory-fresh appearance. The entire process typically takes just 3-5 days with minimal disruption to your daily routine.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Why Refacing Makes Sense
    </h2>
    <p>
      Cabinet refacing delivers the visual impact of brand-new cabinets while offering several distinct advantages. The cost savings are significant — typically 40-60% less than full replacement since you avoid demolition, new cabinet boxes, and the associated plumbing and electrical disconnections. The timeline is dramatically shorter, with most kitchens completed in under a week compared to 6-12 weeks for a full remodel.
    </p>
    <p>
      Refacing is also the environmentally responsible choice. By reusing your existing cabinet boxes, you prevent hundreds of pounds of construction waste from reaching the landfill. And because the process doesn't disturb countertops, backsplash, plumbing, or appliances, there's minimal mess and you maintain full use of your kitchen throughout most of the project.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Material and Style Choices
    </h2>
    <p>
      We offer an extensive palette of door styles and finishes to complement any kitchen aesthetic. Traditional raised-panel doors in cherry or maple create a warm, classic look. Flat-panel (slab) doors in white, gray, or wood-grain laminate deliver a clean contemporary feel. Shaker-style doors remain our most popular option — their simple frame-and-panel construction suits everything from farmhouse to modern transitional kitchens.
    </p>
    <p>
      Finish options include natural wood stains, painted finishes in any color, and textured laminates that replicate the look of wood grain, concrete, or linen. We carry hardware from top brands like Amerock, Top Knobs, and Emtek, offering pulls, knobs, and cup handles in dozens of finishes including brushed nickel, matte black, satin brass, and oil-rubbed bronze.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Our Refacing Process in Seattle
    </h2>
    <p>
      We begin with a free in-home consultation where our designer brings sample doors and veneer swatches directly to your kitchen. Seeing materials against your existing countertops, backsplash, and flooring helps you make confident selections. After finalizing your choices, we take detailed measurements and order your custom components. Most orders arrive within 2-3 weeks, after which our installers complete the transformation in 3-5 days.
    </p>
    <p>
      Many Seattle homeowners pair cabinet refacing with a new countertop or backsplash for a complete kitchen facelift. We can coordinate these additional upgrades to coincide with your refacing project, minimizing overall disruption and ensuring a cohesive design result.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Cost Guide CTA -->
  <div class="bg-accent/5 border border-accent/20 rounded-2xl p-8 my-12">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How Much Does Cabinet Refacing Cost?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Get detailed pricing breakdowns, budget tiers, and money-saving tips in our comprehensive cost guide.</p>
    <a href="/cost-guides/cabinet-refacing-cost/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-accent-hover transition-colors">View Cabinet Refacing Cost Guide →</a>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <Fragment slot="faq">
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
      <Container>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mb-10 text-center">
            Cabinet Refacing FAQs
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                What's the difference between refacing and refinishing?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Refinishing involves sanding and repainting or restaining your existing doors. Refacing goes further — we replace the doors and drawer fronts entirely and apply new veneer to the face frames. Refacing gives you the ability to completely change your cabinet style and offers a more dramatic transformation.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How much does cabinet refacing cost?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Cabinet refacing in the Seattle area typically ranges from $6,000 to $15,000, depending on the number of cabinets, door style, and material selection. This is roughly 40-60% less than the cost of full cabinet replacement. We provide a detailed quote after our free in-home measurement appointment.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Are my cabinets good candidates for refacing?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Most cabinets are good candidates as long as the boxes are structurally sound, level, and free of significant water damage. If you're happy with your current layout and just want to update the look, refacing is an excellent option. During our free consultation, we'll assess your cabinets and let you know honestly whether refacing or replacement is the better investment.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Can I change my cabinet layout during refacing?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Refacing preserves your existing cabinet layout, so it's best suited for homeowners who are satisfied with their current configuration. However, we can add new cabinets to fill gaps, extend uppers to the ceiling, or add a pantry cabinet during the refacing process. For significant layout changes, a full <a href="/services/kitchen-remodeling/" class="text-accent hover:underline">kitchen remodel</a> would be more appropriate.
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Container>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</ServiceLayout>
